This article discusses a Presidential Memorandum issued on April 2, 2020, regarding healthcare and the purchase of ventilators. The memorandum states that due to the threat posed by the coronavirus (SARS-CoV-2), a national emergency was declared, recognizing the strain on healthcare systems. To ensure that healthcare systems have the necessary resources to respond to the spread of COVID-19, the memorandum directs the Secretary of Health and Human Services, in consultation with the Secretary of Homeland Security, to use all available authority under the Defense Production Act to facilitate the supply of materials needed for ventilator production to specific entities. The memorandum also includes general provisions stating that it does not affect existing authorities or create any new rights or benefits.